  "prompt": "Without any external help, how many pennies can you stack before the tower collapses?",
  "response": "The number of pennies you can stack before the tower collapses depends on several factors, including the stability of the base, the precision of your stacking, and the surface on which you're stacking. However, under typical conditions with a stable base and careful stacking, you can usually stack around **35 to 50 pennies** before the tower becomes too unstable and collapses.\n\nHere\u2019s why:\n- Pennies are small and relatively flat, which allows for fairly stable stacking.\n- As you add more pennies, the center of gravity rises, making the stack more prone to toppling.\n- Imperfections in the stacking process (e.g., slight misalignments) accumulate, leading to instability.\n\nIf you\u2019re very precise and have a perfectly flat surface, you might be able to stack slightly more, but eventually, the tower will collapse due to its height and the natural instability of a tall, narrow structure.",
